tspan.tspan: PostGIS is a spatial database extension for PostgreSQL
under the GPLv2+ license. It is written in C and
relies on libraries GEOS and GDAL
for many geometry and raster operations.
PostGIS implements the OGC Spatial Features
for SQL (SFSQL) standard. It goes beyond
thru geography type, and 3D surface and volume support.
and database functions to work with these types
as defined by the SQL-MM: Topo-Geo and Topo-Net.

PostGIS project includes several PostgreSQL extensions.
